Subject: Re: [T2] Steering Woes

At 10:24 AM 6/25/2002, Matthew Libby wrote:
>Under the front of my bus, the long round bars that connect the wheels to 
>the steering box, one on either side.  The R has an adjustment, the L does 
>not.  Should this spin if I grab them and twist them, or is that 
>bad.  (please excuse my blind ignorance on what everything is 
>called.)  Could this by the source of my loose steering??

They can rotate as much as the ball joints will allow, maybe 30 degrees 
each way.  They shouldn't just spin freely.  Loose steering is usually 
caused by a combination of sloppy steering box, loose ball joints and play 
in the pitman arm bushing.

-David

